"Hard-Coded Colors","Enable Sky Colors","Promised Land Sky Color","[BiomesOPlenty] Generated Misc Config!","config/lucky/LuckyBlockProperties.txt","~SEPARATOR~",">IDs",">spawnrate",">recipe",">drops","assets/lucky/LuckyBlockProperties.txt","The Lucky Block encountered and error while trying to perform a function. Erorr report below:","particle","structure","lucky:","SpecialItem","FollowItem","Golem","TravelingTrunk","BrainyZombie","GiantBrainyZombie","Alumentum","PrimalOrb","Wisp","Firebat","FrostShard","ThaumSlime",
"AspectOrb","FallingTaint","TaintSpider","Taintacle","TaintacleTiny","TaintSpore","TaintSwarmer","TaintSwarm","TaintedChicken","TaintedCow","TaintedCreeper","TaintedPig","TaintedSheep","TaintedVillager","Pech","PechBlast","Enchantments","Custom enchantments","Monster_Spawning","Will these mobs spawn","Entity id\'s","Research","Various research related things.","World_Generation","Settings to turn certain world-gen on or off.","World_Regeneration","If a chunk is encountered that skipped TC worldgen, then the game will attempt to regenerate certain world features if they are set to true. CAUTION: Best used for worlds created before you added this mod, and only if you know what you are doing. Backups are advised.",
"Taint","Biomes and effects","biome_taint","Taint biome id","biome_magical_forest","Magical Forest biome id","blue_magical_forest","Set this to true to get the old blue magical forest back.","biome_eerie","Eerie biome id","biome_taint_from_flux","Can Taint be caused by flux effects.","biome_taint_spread","The chance per block update (1 in n) of the Taint biome spreading. Setting it to 0 prevents the spread of Taint biomes.","biome_taint_chance","The chance per chunk (1 in n) of a Taint biome spawning during world gen. Setting it to 0 prevents the spawning of Taint biomes.",
"allow_mirrors","Setting this to false will disable arcane mirror research and crafting recipes.","color_blind","Setting this to true will make certain colors higher contrast or darker to prevent them from being \'invisible\' to color blind people.","crooked","Hate crooked labels, kittens, puppies and all things awesome? If yes, set this to false.","hard_mode_nodes","Negative nodes like hungry, tainted or dark nodes will have additional, much nastier, effects.","wand_dial_bottom","Set to true to have the wand dial display in the bottom left instead of the top left.",
"golem_delay","How many ticks a golem waits between checking for tasks. Setting it higher will save server ticks, but will make the golems slower to react.","golem_link_quality","The fx quality of the line connecting golems to marked blocks. Setting this below 4 deactives the effect entirely.","notification_delay","Determines how fast notifications scroll downards.","notification_max","The maximum amount of notifications that are displayed onscreen.","node_rarity","How rare nodes are in the world. The number means there will be (on average) one node per N chunks.",
"special_node_rarity","The chance of a node being special (pure, dark, unstable, etc.). The number means roughly 1 in N nodes will be special, so setting the number to 5 will mean 1 in 5 nodes may be special.","display_aspects","Item aspects are hidden by default and pressing shift reveals them. Changing this setting to \'true\' will reverse this behaviour and always display aspects unless shift is pressed.","allow_cheat_sheet","Enables a version of the Thauminomicon in creative mode that grants you all the research when you first use it.",
"allow_warded_stone","If set to false, warded stone, doors and glass will just be cosmetic in nature and not have its hardened properties (everyone will be able to break it with equal ease).","golem_chest_interact","If set to true golems will attempt to play the chest opening animations and sounds whenever they interact with them.","portablehole_blacklist","This is a comma-delimited list of any block-id\'s the portable hole is not allowed to pass through.","generate_aura_nodes","generate_structures","generate_cinnibar_ore",
"generate_amber_ore","generate_infused_stone","generate_trees","generate_taint","regen_key","This key is used to keep track of which chunk have been generated/regenerated. Changing it will cause the regeneration code to run again, so only change it if you want it to happen. Useful to regen only one world feature at a time.","aura_nodes","structures","cinnibar_ore","amber_ore","infused_stone","trees","taint","research_difficulty","0 = normal, -1 = easy (all research items are directly purchased with RP), 1 = Hard (all research items need to be solved via the research table)",
