"II ","IR ","RI ","blockCrystalFlux","FFAA00","00FF00","PopOffs","These Settings effect the digits that bounce off mobs when they take damage.","Portrait","These Settings effect the current health portrait window on the hud.","PopOffs.Behavior","This subcategory holds behavioral settings to do with PopOffs.","Portrait.Behavior","This subcategory holds behavioral settings to do with Portraits.","PopOffs.Appearance","This subcategory holds appearance settings to do with PopOffs.","Portrait.Appearance","This subcategory holds appearance settings to do with Portraits.",
"Internal","Don\'t Modify these settings unless explicitly told to or if you know what you are doing.\n This could result in the lose of settings or an unexpected crash.","How long the damage indicator lasts before disappearing. Defaults to 12. Decimals not accepted, whole numbers only.","Portrait_xPos","This is typically set from the repositioning Gui in game, but added here for modpacks.","Portrait_Skin","The Currently Selected Skin Path.","Portrait_yPos","Always_Render","When true, the particles will always render in front, otherwise, only if you can directly see the mob.",
"UpdateBehavior","0 = Disable, 1 = Only alert when update is available, 2 = Normal Behavior.","Transparency","Number between 1.0 and 0.0 that controls how transparent the digits are. 1.0 means no transparency.","Lock_Mob_Position","When true, mobs in the portrait are locked in place. When false, they turn the same same as they are turning in the world.","Gui_Scale","Change the size of the portrait preview.","Use_Skin","Use the Fancy Skin when drawing the gui. Set to false to use the old one.","Build_TexturePack_Font",
"When building the font file for the damage indicator, use the texture pack specific font. Default true, set to false to use the default font.","Scale_Smoothing_Filter","Apply the Scale Smoothing filter to the font. Accepts any number between 2.0 and 4.0. All other numbers disable the filter. Defaults to 0.0(disabled). The Scale filter induces a smoother font, but can introduce fuzziness as a consequence. High values may increase startup time significantly when applied to high resolution fonts, or run java out of memory entirely.",
"The color of the digits. Must use a 3 byte 16-bit(hex) RGB value here, also known as html notation. Defaults to FFFF00(Yellow).","Heal_Color","The color of the digits on heals. Must use a 3 byte 16-bit(hex) RGB value here, also known as html notation. Defaults to 00FF00(Green).","Range","The range that mouse overing mobs will display their health.","Enable","Set to false to Disable.","Gravity","Change this to change the speed that the damage indicators fall, low numbers prevent falling numbers entirely. All positive numbers accepted, 0.8 is default.",
"Set this to false to disable damage pop offs. Typically Set using the in game gui.(\'.\' Period is the default keybinding)","Bounce_Strength","This sets how powerful the initial bounce is. All positive numbers accepted, 1.5 is default.","This sets how far to send damage alerts to clients.","The size of the digits that bounce off mobs, defaults to 3.0","Portrait_Lifetime","How long the Portrait will stay after you are no longer targetting a mob. -1 to last forever or until the mob is unloaded.","Show Potion Effects",
"DebugHidesWindow","Should the debug window(F3) Hide the portrait window.","SupressBossHealth","Hide boss health bars.","AlternateRenderMethod","If the portrait is not visible for you or renders incorrectly, set this to true.","HighCompatibilityMode","Only set this to true if you have rendering problems. It can decrease preformance.","ShowCriticalHits","Pop off critical when a critical strike lands.","useDropShadows","Use drop shadows on popoffs.","Enable_Depth_Test","When true, objects in the environment can block the numbers",
