"tempid","Export","Copy template(care, can overwrite your buildings)","Size red","Size yellow","File name","Set AI mode \"","\" to ","dartcraft:paper","Allow: ","Owner Only","Trap Mode","Storage Units may be recolored with Shapeless Recipes using dyes.","Storage Units will not be accessible to other players if their access is set to Closed.","Storage Units can be upgraded with the Storage upgrade to increase their storage capacity.","Storage Units can use Item Cards in the same way as Force Packs, excepting that unupgraded Item Cards will do nothing.",
"Upgrading a Storage Unit with the Sturdy upgrade will allow its inventory to persist when broken.","EU: ","Force Panel"," Mk3","The Force Grinder may be recolored with IC2 painters.","The Force Grinder can run on medium voltage and functions much like an Induction Furnace as it idles at 1 EU/t and functions at 16 EU/t.","The Force Grinder will use Force Grinding recipes first, and IC2 Macerator recipes if no recipe is found.","This machine may be broken and moved without losing any of the data on it.","Energy: ",
"Speed:","The Force Extractor is an advanced version of the Extractor.  That\'s about it.","The Force Extractor is recolorable with IC2 painters.","The Force Extractor can run on medium voltage and functions much like an Induction Furnace as it idles at 1 EU/t and functions at 16 EU/t.","The Force Crusher is an advanced version of the Compressor.  That\'s about it.","The Force Crusher is recolorable with IC2 painters.","The Force Crusher can run on medium voltage and functions much like an Induction Furnace as it idles at 1 EU/t and functions at 16 EU/t.",
"Force Generators may be recolored with dyes or IC2 Painters.","Force Generators retain their fuel when idling and data when broken, like Force Furnaces.","Force Furnaces can be upgraded to Generators without losing stored items or fuel.","Force Generators generate the same amount of EU that normal Generators do, but they can also burn Force Engine liquids.","Lava burns equivalently to Geothermal Generators and is used as a base when calculating other liquids\' burn times.","Force Generators function more efficiently with the Heat upgrade.",
"The Speed upgrade will increase the Max Output in EU/t, so be careful when using this upgrade.","Speed also increases the rate at which fuel is burned, but does not increase efficiency.","Freezing will allow the Force Generator to run on Force Engine Throttles.","Force Generator","Force Furnaces may be recolored with Shapeless Recipes using dyes.","Force Furnaces retain their fuel when idling, unlike vanilla furnaces.","Force Furnaces smelt items faster than vanilla furnaces, but use the same amount of fuel.",
"Force Furnaces retain their contents and fuel when picked up, so there is no need to Force Wrench them.","Force Furnaces can be socketed with an Upgrade Core to enhance their abilities.  Try Speed, Rainbow or even Freezing cores.","To de-socket an upgrade core simply shift right click the slot to destroy it.","A Frozen Core is a good way to quickly make stone for less resources than smelting all that cobble would take.","Force Furnaces can be upgraded to grind ores and other objects just as a grinding imbued Force Pickaxe would.",
"An Experience Core will dramatically increase the amount of experience received from smelting items.","Placing an Experience Tome in an adjacent IInventory will automatically store the experience received from smelted items in the tome.","Force Furnaces will return Empty Buckets when running on buckets of lava.","Force Furnace","Liquid Force (","Save","Redoing slots: ","Dimension ","The Force Infuser can be used to imbue your Force Tools with special upgrades that range from vanilla Fortune to auto grinding or even wacky side-effects.",
"The Force Infuser requires both Liquid Force and a significant amount of Minecraft Joules to run.","The Force Infuser will take one level of experience from you for each upgrade material you want to use.","Healing seems to have the opposite effect on undead creatures.","Force Bows now have toggleable modes, just grab one and shift right click to change modes.","Most Force Tools now have an \"Area\" mode that can be toggled by right-clicking with the tool in your hands.  It may be slower, but it sure breaks a lot of blocks!  Be sure to mind your durability.",
"Upgrade materials show their upgrade in this Gui as a secondary tooltip in yellow.  If a third tooltip is active that is the Tier at which the upgrade is unlocked.","Yellow question marks in a tooltip means the Upgrade Tome has not yet seen this upgrade.","Upgrade Tomes are created by right clicking a Book with a Force Rod.","Experience Tomes can hold any amount of experience for the player, and are tradable to boot.","Be careful with that button!  Once you press it the only way to stop it is with a quick Force-Wrenching.",
"Force Armor must be crafted out of Force Ingots.","Additional upgrade slots are unlocked by advancing your Upgrade Tome in tier.","Ender Bows only work on players if PVP is enabled.","You\'re going to need Force Sticks, why not try your Force Rod on a sapling?","Use your Force Shears on other animals.","You can place Force Gems directly into the Force Infuser and Force Engine to get some Liquid Force, although engines are terribly ineffective at extracting Liquid Force.","Force Shard?  What\'s all this junk?  Force Shards provide 1 bucket of Liquid Force inside all DartCraft devices, but in the infuser they also give the Upgrade Tome a bonus 10 points.",
"Using differing upgrades will help level your Upgrade Tome faster.","Force Rods are upgraded directly in the Force Infuser.","Return","Next Page","Previous Page","Go","§eLiquid Force§f ("," MJ","Unknown Upgrade","] Tier: "," Mlvl: ","Information","clipventory","Movement: ","Stance: ","§nRepair and Modification","Durability:"," Heart","Attack: ","Loss: ","Bonus: ","Draw Speed: ","Arrow Speed: ","Mining Speeds: ","Base Attack:","Harvest Levels:","Shortbow Attack:","Usage Speed: ","Modifiers:","Weight: ","Modifiers remaining: ",
